text.author: Techtonica
text.title: Welcome to the Techtonica curriculum!
text.summary1: (human1) This curriculum for Techtonica, a non-profit project offering hands on tech training, details a 15 week syllabus covering developer tools, webpages (HTML, CSS), JavaScript at React, Web APIs, databases, testing, data structures and algorithms, an Eventonica project and full stack practice, as well as a career week and assessments.
text.summary2: (claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) Techtonica's free tech training program teaches full-stack web development using JavaScript over 15+ weeks, covering topics from developer tools and HTML/CSS to algorithms and career preparation, culminating in a final full-stack web application project.
text.summary3: (gpt4o) Techtonica offers a free, intensive, hands-on tech training program focused on full-stack web development with JavaScript, aimed at unemployed or underemployed individuals, emphasizing workplace readiness, self-directed learning, and project-based experiences to facilitate smooth transitions into software engineering careers.
text.summary4: (Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) Techtonica is a free tech training and job placement program that provides intensive, hands-on full-stack web development training using JavaScript, with a focus on project-based learning and collaboration.
text.summary5: (Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct) Techtonica's free tech training program covers full-stack web development from JavaScript to databases and project work, preparing participants for the tech industry with hands-on experience and collaboration, culminating in a final full-stack web application project.
